LDS-cached x for Q8_0 wave decode matmul

## Status
Proposed

## Goal
Load x cooperatively into LDS once per block, then have all NROWS waves read from LDS instead of each wave re-reading from global memory. Saves (NROWS-1)/NROWS of x global reads.

## Context
File: ds4_rocm.c:559, `rocm_matmul_q8_0_wave_##NROWS##_kernel`

Current decode kernel: NROWS=8, blockDim=256 (8 waves of 32 lanes). Each wave independently reads x[4096] from global to compute its output row dot product. With 8 waves, x is read 8x redundantly.
- x: 4096 floats = 16 KiB -> fits exactly in <=16 KiB LDS budget per block
- w: each wave reads different weight rows (no redundancy there)

Tradeoff: LDS staging costs __syncthreads() + reduces occupancy if LDS budget per block was the limiter. On RDNA 3.5 with 40 CUs, 8 waves/block at 16 KiB LDS still allows 2 blocks/CU (depending on register pressure).

Earlier benchmark (L2431 comment) showed LDS variant 4x slower: "48 vs 185 GiB/s on 4096^2". That was likely from a different codebase state. Re-measure from current baseline (~75 GiB/s decode matvec).

